First Department,

September 1968

(September 12, 1968) In the Matter of Nathan Straus, Appellant-Respondent, v. James M. Power et al., Constituting the Board of Elections of the City of New York, Respondents, and Jacob H. Gilbert, Respondent-Appellant.

Judgment unanimously affirmed, without costs and without disbursements. No opinion. Concur — Botein, P. J., Stevens, Eager, Tilzer and Capozzoli, JJ.
